ADR-02 — Use PostgreSQL as the Relational Database
Status: Accepted
Context
Complaints, users, audit logs, and tenants require relational integrity, foreign keys, indexing, and ACID consistency.
Decision
Use PostgreSQL as the primary data store.
Rationale
•	Excellent support for relational data and complex queries.
•	Strong compatibility with Django ORM.
•	Reliable for multi-tenant filtering and reporting workloads.
Consequences
Positive: Highly reliable, scalable, supports indexing, transactions.
Negative: Requires more setup than SQLite.
